items.name: GAME DEV TOOLS 01 / GRID
items.description:
If you find our articles informative, please follow me to receive updates. It would be even better if you could also follow our ko-fi, where there are many more articles and tutorials that I believe would be very beneficial for you!

如果你觉得我们的文章有料，请关注我获得更新通知，如果能同时关注我们的 ko-fi 就更好了，那里有多得多的文章和教程! 相信能使您获益良多.

For collaboration and article reprint inquiries, please send an email to aigarlic@pm.me
合作和文章转载 请发送邮件至 aigarlic@pm.me

By: Ash0080

If you like my work, feel free to submit your pictures and give it a five-star rating. It would definitely make my day and bring a smile to my face.

What?

This is the first model in the GRID series, where GRID stands for Game Roles Instant Design. I have written an article discussing these concepts, so I won't go into detail here.

https://civitai.com/articles/1411

Essentially, GRID is designed to help artists quickly prototype character designs. It is first and foremost a tool, and secondly, it is a multiple concepts LoRa that includes three sub-concepts, which can cover a significant portion of use cases without the need for additional LoRa.

Why?

First of all, there are currently very few LoRa that are similar to this one, not in terms of the Chibi type, but in terms of its focus on professional applications. The reason why the first model is Chibi is that there are relatively few Chibi types available at the moment. Additionally, the Chibi has a better tolerance and is more convenient for me to conduct experiments. As the first LoRa in this series, I believe this theme is quite fitting.

How?

Actually, the basic usage of this LoRa is quite simple and easy to get started with. However, there are some advanced features hidden in this LoRa that I have documented in a 18-page user manual on our Ko-fi page. (For example, the two hidden sub-concepts that can change the style, and others.)
If you are interested, you can take a look.

https://ko-fi.com/post/Game-Roles-Instant-Design--chibimonstermecha-3i-V7V4NKQPC

中文版

https://ko-fi.com/post/%E6%B8%B8%E6%88%8F%E8%A7%92%E8%89%B2%E7%9E%AC%E6%97%B6%E8%AE%BE%E8%AE%A1%E5%B7%A5%E5%85%B701--chibimonstermecha-3-in-1-LoRa-%E5%B7%A5%E4%BD%9C%E6%B5%81-X8X5NKPR1

Of course, if you only use its simplest chibi concept, it is still easy to use without the user manual.

items.name: Astro Beauties Lora [ alien girl / monster / body paint ]
items.description:
If you wanna know what's this about in case u have questions, scroll down to Q/A section.

Prompt: alien,colored skin, (green skin:1.3), space, dress, creepy, details,masterpiece, <lora-name-here:1>
Lora weight: 0.5-1.0 (did not test under 0.5, but from what I saw it can
ALL Booru Tags for prompts here

Full Negative prompt: blue skin,easynegative, (badhandv4), lr, beard, curly, veiny, muscular, ((bodybuilder)), facial hair, mustache, lowres, fewer fingers, out of frame, jpeg artifacts, ugly, duplicate, morbid,mutilated, extra fingers, mutated hands, poorly drawn hands, poorly drawn face, mutation, deformed, blurry, dehydrated, bad anatomy, bad proportions, extra limbs, cloned face, disfigured, gross proportions, malformed limbs, missing arms, missing legs, extra arms, extra legs, fused fingers,

Tips/extra Negative tag prompts: blue skin is there at the start because 70% of all images contain blue skin, also you might get helmets or fish girl ears or pointy ears, or cloaks, and lots of bodysuits, so you might want to add these as well: (cloak),(siren),(fish ears),(fat),(helmet), pointy ears, (black bodysuit:1.3),high breasts, breast from abdomen,bald,hairless,feminine

Settings
It should work with your usual settings but here are mine:

  • Sampler: Euler a (tested also on DPM ++ 2M SDE Karras and it's decent)

  • Size: 512-512 / 512-768 (I do mainly in 512-768)

  • Clip skip: 2 (didn't test clip skip 1)

  • Sampling Steps: 20-30 (I use 30 all the time)

  • Hiresfix upscaler: R-ESRGAN 4x Anime6B on 2x, steps: 20, denoise 0.5 (I didn't test higher or lower than 0.5).

  • Cfg scale: 6-30 (I use mainly 7, but I noticed on certain prompts/seeds, it produce better or more interesting results on different CFG. Also certain models or vae might make it look worse if you go higher CFG)


Q: What's this Lora about?
A: I'd like to know that myself but overall you can make Alien girls(and human skin girls) that look good, with vibrant colors, a splash of colors everywhere. You can also Make male or weird stuff that looks more alien-like. But I did not include weird-like aliens because the goal is Human-like girls that look somewhat alien/monster/weird while keeping the human sexy/cute factor in. (To be honest the images I used in training are more impressive than what this Lora can do, click here)

Q: Can you add multiple lora in one prompt?
A: Yes, but it's a pain in the ass(you gotta pick a model that is able to respond great to multiple Lora), i'm no master at 2-3 lora in the same prompt, and it takes many generation to get something that I like, and even then I am no near the level of what someone pro could make with a good prompt and negative prompt.

Q: The girls don't even look alien it's more a splash of paint everywhere. I demand my Alien!
A: Yeah sorry buddy, I created this Lora because when I searched: "monster girl", I got MONSTER GIRLS, like the ones u see in hentai, half horse or half snake. Those make me feel grossed out. Then I searched "alien" and they had literally realistic creepy aliens.
I wanted something somewhat anime style with high quality, I wanted the girls to look good no matter what (which means I can focus on writing (ugly/creepy/monster) and I still get cute/sexy stuff). It's pretty much a mix between what an alien or monster should be and a human (anthropomorphic)


Q:How Many Images I used for training?
A: 699, 50% of those are blue skin, rest is other type of colors and added also human skin, 90% are girls, 2-3% are boys, rest are weird shapes and creatures. The main things are: subject full body front view, it also has full body back view, side view, standing on things, and floating in the air

items.name: Headless Girl | Concept LoRA
items.description:
So no head? *smashes phone*

Basically get rid of head completely and replace it with a stump.

Trained with Anything 4.5

I used Additional Networks extension for LoRAs so the sample images so it may not include lora:name:1 or something like that. They are all available in here btw.

Trigger word is "headless"

Recommendation:

  • Works the best around weight 0.8 - 1.

  • You should not use any prompt related to facial features and hairstyles (e.g. blue eyes, purple hair, smile, etc)

  • May generate some abomination so you probably need some negative embedding.

  • Could be compatible with some LoRA that doesn't register the character appearance by default (LoRA that needs multiple tags to generate a proper character)

  • Might not work well with realistic models.

  • CLIP SKIP: 2

  • CFG Scale: 7 or 8, can work on higher scale with Dynamic Thresholding (CFG Scale Fix)

items.name: Omega Centauri
items.description:
I don't know why people want it this but I guess it's because the curiosity of the unknown. It actually helped me to improve it a bit though so can't complain :D

Name implies one of our galaxy's satellite the Omega Centauri globular star cluster. But it's just for the sake of naming the checkpoint.

Okay here it is. This checkpoint mainly focuses realism but with right prompting you might get semi realistic results as well. I made two versions and their purposes as follows:

Omega Centauri Cocktail - Alpha = The main checkpoint. Very flexible and it behaves well with loras, lycorises and textual inversions. Default it is mainly asian centric because most merges derive from them.

Omega Centauri Cocktail - Proxima = This checkpoint is just for fun. It's main strength is to generate doll like women. You can go wild with this but I don't know it's limit. It might not be custom model friendly so be aware.

VAE : vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned.ckpt baked in.

Now what it contains:

Omega Centauri Cocktail - Alpha:

  • Original non public version: endless reality_v2, darksun, edge of realism, rev animated, realmix, fantasticmix, photon, magicmix realistic and realAliceMixv1

  • This version : Magicmix realistic, realalicemix, ultimate diffusion, JAM, endlessreality and with lowRa model baked in with 0.25 weight. Then original and this version mixed with 50/50 ratio.

Omega Centauri Cocktail - Proxima:

  • This version : Original non public version + fantasticmix, revanimated with russian doll likeness at 0.25 and korean doll likeness at 0.22 weight baked in + lowRa

This is basically it. How I use it:

CFG Scale: 6-7

Sample steps : 20

Sampler : DPM++2M Karras

Hiresfix : 0.3-0.5 denoise with 4x_foolhardy_Remacri upscaler and hires steps at 10.

Base prompts:

Positive : After your prompt add BREAK best quality, deep shadows, 8k, dslr, Kodak ektar 100, Fujifilm XT3, F4, 1/800s, ISO 100, RAW. You can add or remove some of it.

Negative : Before your prompt add (worst quality:1.5), (low quality:1.5), (nsfw:1.4), (naked:1.4) BREAK your prompt here.

Hope you find it useful and for those who asking for this please share your results :)

Support me on buymeacoffee if you like my work.
